<section id="command-inportb">
<title>INPORTB</title>
<indexterm><primary>INPORTB</primary></indexterm>

<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term>Synopsis</term>
<listitem>
<synopsis><command>INPORTB</command> <parameter>portid</parameter></synopsis>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Description</term>
<listitem>

<para>
Reads one byte from the port specified by <parameter>portid</parameter> and output the data as an integer.
The <parameter>portid</parameter> input specifies a "Hardware" port.
</para>

<para>
Do not confuse INPORTB with <link linkend="command-portopen">PORTOPEN</link> and <link linkend="command-portreadchar">PORTREADCHAR</link> which are for communications through the serial and parallel ports.
</para>

</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Example</term>
<listitem>

<programlisting><userinput>SHOW INPORTB 198</userinput>
130
</programlisting>

</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>See Also</term>
<listitem><simplelist>
<member><link linkend="command-inport">INPORT</link></member>
<member><link linkend="command-outportb">OUTPORTB</link></member>
</simplelist></listitem>
</varlistentry>

</variablelist>
</section>
